  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Trade shape",
      "text": "The kingdom does not depend on war. It depends on roads, ports, customs houses, and the appetite of its elites."
    },
    {
      "title": "Social pressure",
      "text": "Eveneld and Bowemor remain relatively poor. Dalfaros, Iselnes, and Dalwart concentrate gold, imported luxuries, and pricing power."
    },
    {
      "title": "External dependence",
      "text": "Kudland is a luxury source; Devenesia is a demand sink. Both strengthen Ruimdal’s trade centrality, but also expose it to outside shocks."
    }
  ]
